{
  "circuit": {
    "description": "Series RC bench for capacitor geometric-cap T3 temperature-sweep parity. Capacitor uses the geometric model (cj, cjsw, W, L set; positional capacitance NOT set) plus TC1=0.01 so effective capacitance folds with ambient temperature. ngspice's captemp.c:55-68 selects the geometric base (cj*(W-narrow)*(L-short) + 2*cjsw*((L-short)+(W-narrow))) and captemp.c:86-89 applies factor = 1 + TC1*dT + TC2*dT^2; digiTS's computeTemperature does the same. With W=L=1mm, cj=1e-3 F/m^2, cjsw=0: base C = 1nF. R=1k -> tau=1us. AcVoltageSource(1V, 1kHz) drives. Used at T in {300.15K, 350K, 400K}.",
